  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Light Rain
  author: Seo Geo-jeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    A light rain washes away the lingering heat,
    As cool winds stir the ancient branches.
    Through the broken window, the moon appears,
    On the weathered wall, half a poem is inscribed.

    On the traveler's road, few companions remain,
    In human life, parting is the common thread.
    Why is it that through all the night's dreams,
    I always journey homeward without end?
  footnotes:
    - The 'half a poem' on the wall suggests the incompleteness of journeys and lives cut short by departure.
    - The progression from natural imagery (rain, wind, moon) to human longing reflects the poet's meditation on transience and homesickness during exile or travel.
